title: NotebookLM now supports over 50 languages NotebookLM, Google‚Äôs AI-powered note-taking tool, now supports audio overviews in over 50 languages‚Äîat no cost. Designed to function like ChatGPT for your documents, it allows users to upload files, generate summaries, and ask questions based on the content. With this update, users can change the output language by navigating to Settings on the NotebookLM site and selecting from the available options. The multilingual functionality was tested using Little Women in both English and French. The platform generated summaries and responses in both languages, but notable differences emerged: the English version produced a longer 18-minute audio overview and supported Interactive Mode, which enables follow-up questions. The French version, in contrast, lacked that feature and offered a much shorter overview. Other users have encountered similar inconsistencies. One reported that switching the output language to Bengali caused citation links to stop functioning, making it difficult to verify sources. In response, the NotebookLM team acknowledged the issue and confirmed that a fix is in progress. The update reflects broader efforts to expand AI accessibility across languages, though current limitations show that full feature parity across all languages is still a work in progress. #notebooklm, #googleai, #ainotetaker
